==============================================Filtering/ Ignoring properties in JSON serialization and deserialization.=========================================================================

@JsonIgnore used at method (setter, getter) or field - To ignore that property - @JsonIgnore
@JsonIgnoreProperties used at at the class level - To ignore one or more properties. - @JsonIgnoreProperties(value = {"id","firstName"})
@JsonIgnoreType used at the class level - To ignores all properties of class. - @JsonIgnoreType
